---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Nathan Rasmussen and the custom design, prototyping, 3D printing, painting, finishing, and assembly work behind Nathan Rasmussen Design."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container about-grid">
      <figure class="about-media">
        <img
          src="/images/portfolio/nathan-deer.jpg"
          alt="Nathan with a custom deer display piece."
          width="1200"
          height="800"
        />
      </figure>
      <div class="stack">
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1>I like making ideas real.</h1>
        <p>
          I design, prototype, 3D print, paint, and assemble custom awards, props,
          and display pieces. Some projects need original CAD work, some need adaptation,
          and others come down to careful printing, finishing, and assembly. My goal is to
          create pieces that feel intentional, polished, and worth keeping.
        </p>
        <p>
          My background is in physics and software, so I tend to approach projects by breaking
          them into parts: what it needs to do, how it should look, what has to be modeled,
          what needs to be tested, and what will make it hold up in the real world. Some
          projects need original CAD work. Some need a practical prototype. Some just need
          patience, cleanup, and careful finishing.
        </p>
        <p>
          I have made awards, display pieces, organizers, prototypes, and personal projects.
          The common thread is that I like the whole process: talking through the idea, making
          the first version, improving the details, and ending up with something solid enough
          to hand to someone.
        </p>
        <p>
          I love Seattle, and my favorite project so far was building a 5 1/2-foot-tall
          Space Needle. It took about 100 hours of design and modeling, 750 hours of printing,
          and another 100 hours of gluing, sanding, and painting.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
